title: For Sale:  Custom CZ-52 with Novak Target sights and ammo
postcontent:
PRICE DROP for quick sale. This fine single-action handgun was made in 1954 and imported in the early 90's (no import marks). Included are three magazines with aftermarket extended floorplates for fast reloads, the original holster, and the option to include 520 rounds of ammo. The CZ-52 is widely accepted to be a more robust design than the TT-33, utilizing the roller delayed-blowback action like the MG-42, HK G3, and MP5. The original rollers have been replaced with new hardened steel ones. The original firing pin has also been replaced with a hardened steel model that won't break when dry fired. The original tiny fixed sights were milled off and 1911 style Novak adjustable target sights installed- the difference is amazing compared to the factory sights. The original Bakelite grips were sealed and then painted black. The parkerized finish on the frame is in 90%+ original condition and the slide has been coated in Dark Parkerizing Gray Alumahyde II rustproof gun coating (properly cured) so it can be carried IWB without worrying about rusting from sweat. Function wise, I have never had any malfunction in 500 rounds. The decocker/safety works properly and the hammer does not contact the firing pin when decocking.

It fires the potent 7.62x25mm tokarev round which will defeat both sides of a threat level IIa bullet proof vest or one side of a level II vest with normal target grade FMJ's. The now banned 320 (of 520) hardened steel core AP rounds I am including will defeat all soft body armor up to level III. These rounds are legal to own in all 50 states, they can just no longer be imported into the country or manufactured.

The gun has a very thin profile and can be concealed as easily and sometimes better than a 1911. If you're expecting bad guys with body armor and want better penetration than a .357 SIG, this is the gun for you. Would make a perfect glove box gun to shoot through glass and sheet metal if needed to. Hollow points are available online if you are concerned about over-penetration.

The ammo available is:
100 rounds of banned Norinco mild steel core non-corrosive FMJ
100 rounds of S&B indoor range safe new production non-corrosive reloadable FMJ
320 rounds of mixed Hintenberger and another European manufacture 1955 and 1962 production hardened steel core AP. The finest 7.62 ammo ever available to civilians, last available in 1990. This ammo is mildly corrosive like most surplus stuff. It is very clean brass cased and berdan primed. I have shot through 1/4" steel plate like it wasn't there, and I have seen it shred Kevlar helmets.

Besides defense, this is one heck of a fun gun to shoot. It sounds like a .44 magnum going off, and it has the recoil of a .45 1911. Minute of bad guy accuracy out to 150 yards from a bench, and very flat shooting. 9mm luger drop-in conversion barrels are available online.

I'm looking for a new toy, so this one has to go. 

$400 cash or $500 trade for the pistol and three mags and holster.
$600 cash or $700 trade OBO for the above plus all the ammo.

Ammo is not for sale without the gun.

The sights, modern steel upgrades, and magazines are worth $400 alone.

I am open to trades and trades plus cash for firearms and military related equipment, silver, cool stuff etc. What do you have? Worst I can say is no thanks. I am NOT interested in your used SCUBA gear, marijuana grow lights, or fish tanks.

If you are reading this, it's still for sale. 

Will meet at the Tulalip Cabelas in Marysville, WA only. Will ship overnight to your FFL at your expense for $50. Ammo ships separately for $20. Qualifies for C&R FFL sale if you have one of those and can go through normal mail that way for $15, ammo still $20.

I am a CPL holder and will only sell to US citizens 18 and older with valid ID and bill of sale. If you have a CPL or WAC card, no bill of sale is necessary.

Thank you for looking, and remember to vote no on I-594 this November.

title: For Sale:  Rare, Vintage Colt CS Gas Pen Gun (.38 cal)
postcontent:
Purchased new in Memphis in the late 1960’s. New, never-fired, in original dealer box with cardstock header intact (original price: $6.95). Made by Colt in Hartford, CT. Pen gun is stamped “COLT” (see pic). Appears to be aluminum (based on weight), but is finished in bright brass. 

Pen gun comes with original box, foam lining, 2 original, unused CS tear gas rounds and mounting bracket with screw for attaching under desk, at bedside, etc.

Cartridges are screwed onto the muzzle of the pen and the cocking knob pulled back and locked into position. To fire, simply thumb the knob down and the internal spring drives the firing pin into the primer.

THIS DOES NOT FIRE PROJECTILES/BULLETS. It is manufactured for gas cartridges only. Conversion to fire live ammo is not recommended.

This is classified as a non-lethal weapon, but not as an AOW (Any Other Weapon), thus the buyer would not need any paperwork to own the pen gun (if the gun were converted by a Class 2 manufacturer to fire live ammo, it would need to be registered with the BATFE and a $5.00 tax stamp would be required).

Incredible collector’s item. It is becoming increasingly rare to find these. 

Buyer must be over 18 years of age and please check local laws before considering purchase.

Price is firm (unless you're local, in which case I'll knock a bit off, seeing as how I won't have to ship it, and I'll try to look out for neighbors). If shipping is required, buyer must agree to pay shipping cost. I ship only to the lower 48 states.
